dc_description_s: U.S.G.S. 7.5 minute series (topographic) North Decimal Degree 39.750000. South Decimal Degree 39.625000. East Decimal Degree -74.500000. West Decimal Degree -74.625000. Alternate title: Jenkins, N. J. Polyconic projection. Universal transverse Mercator grids are shown. Relief shown by 10 feet contour interval and spot heights. Datum is mean sea level. "Mapped, edited and published by the United States Geological Survey. Control by USC&GS, USCE, and New Jersey Geodetic Survey. Culture and drainage in part compiled from aerial photograpghs taken 1951. Topography by planetable surveys 1955 and 1956." Map is temporarily filed in the Reserve Course Materials Collection.
dc_title_s: Jenkins Quadrangle, New Jersey 7.5 minute series (topographic)
